## What is a Medical Loan?

A medical loan is a personal loan specifically designed to cover healthcare costs. Unlike using credit cards or draining savings, it gives you a lump sum upfront with predictable monthly payments.

**Common uses:**
- Emergency surgery (heart, accident injuries, appendectomy)
- Cancer treatment and chemotherapy
- Dental procedures (implants, braces, root canals)
- Fertility treatments (IVF, specialist consultations)
- Elective surgery (eye surgery, cosmetic procedures)
