## Common Questions (FAQ)

**Q: Can I use a medical loan for alternative treatments?**
Yes. The loan is cash â€” you can use it for TCM, homeopathy, overseas treatment, or any medical expense. Lenders don't restrict how you spend it.

**Q: Do I need collateral?**
No. Most medical loans are unsecured personal loans. You don't need to pledge property or assets.

**Q: Can I pay off early without penalty?**
Depends on the lender. Some charge 1-3% prepayment penalties. Others allow free early repayment after 6-12 months. Check your agreement.

**Q: What if the treatment costs more than expected?**
You can apply for a top-up loan (additional financing). This is easier with your existing lender since you've already proven creditworthiness.

**Q: Can foreigners get medical loans in Malaysia?**
Yes, but it's harder. Requirements:
- Malaysian PR or valid work permit
- Employed in Malaysia for at least 2 years
- Higher income requirements (RM 5,000+ minimum)

**Q: Will this affect my credit score?**
Yes, but not negatively if you pay on time. A well-managed loan actually improves your credit over time (shows financial responsibility).

